law.text:
A District Court has the following authority provided in the Health - General Article:
Under Title 8 of that article, the authority to commit an individual for detoxification or for observation, evaluation, or treatment of alcoholism;
Under Title 8 of that article, the authority to commit an individual for observation, evaluation, or treatment of drug abuse;
Under Title 10 of that article, the authority to order emergency evaluation of an individual for a mental disorder; and
Under Title 12 of that article, authority as to the competency or sanity of a criminal defendant.
